      ## Preprocessors are built-in

      The preprocessors you want are already built-in—no need to configure anything. Create a new `.scss` file, and it will automatically be preprocessed as Sass. Write a new `.js` file, and automatically include `require` modules via Browserify.

      - Sass (Very fast via Node-sass and Libsass)
      - LESS
      - Stylus
      - CoffeeScript
      - Jade
      - EJS
      - Markdown

      - Flexible metadata
      - Autoprefixer
      - Browserify
      - Minification
      - Source Maps (?)

      ## Multi-platform

      - OS X
